<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1400,1426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Placement.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[290,428,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Anthribinae">Anthribinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis box="[440,597,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">incertae sedis</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1866" box="[738,899,1401,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[738,899,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Diastatotropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1138,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Apatenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="world">A world</taxonomicName>
catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C." box="[468,827,1436,1462]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" refId="ref7924" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. (1999) A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (Excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Entomopraxis S. C. P. Edition, Barcelona, 315 pp." type="book" year="1999">Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal 1999</bibRefCitation>
) in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal, 1999" authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cappadocini">
Cappadocini 
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C." pageId="1" pageNumber="31" refId="ref7924" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. (1999) A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (Excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Entomopraxis S. C. P. Edition, Barcelona, 315 pp." type="book" year="1999">Alonso-Zarazaga &amp; Lyal, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a tribe established in this work. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lyal, C. H. C. &amp; Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A." box="[719,1087,1472,1499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" pagination="21 - 31" refId="ref8328" refString="Lyal, C. H. C. &amp; Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (2006) Addenda and corrigenda to ' A World Catalogue of Families and Genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) '. 2. Zootaxa, 1202, 21 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1202.1.2" type="journal article" year="2006">Lyal &amp; Alonso-Zarazaga (2006)</bibRefCitation>
later transferred this genus to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[151,285,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Anthribinae">Anthribinae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[293,449,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">incertae sedis</emphasis>
. With respect to the differing views on the concept of tribes of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[1295,1432,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anthribidae</taxonomicName>
, we provisionally keep this genus as 
<emphasis box="[556,711,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">incertae sedis</emphasis>
; a more detailed concept of tribal arrangement will be published in further studies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Recognition.</emphasis>
Body oval to elongate. Rostrum extended apically, with one central longitudinal carina or without this carina (in the case of 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse, 1882" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1882" box="[447,825,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidipennis">
<emphasis box="[447,614,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. nitidipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse, C. O." box="[622,825,1652,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref9647" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. (1882) Descriptions of new Coleoptera from Madagascar (Anthribidae and Longicornia). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 10, 43 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938209459664" type="journal article" year="1882">Waterhouse, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse, 1882" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1882" box="[882,1247,1652,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[882,1032,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. planifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse, C. O." box="[1040,1247,1652,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" pagination="43 - 47" refId="ref9647" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. (1882) Descriptions of new Coleoptera from Madagascar (Anthribidae and Longicornia). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 10, 43 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938209459664" type="journal article" year="1882">Waterhouse, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and two lateral carinae, or lateral carinae absent (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[600,700,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[600,700,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryzna &amp; Banar" authorityYear="2022" box="[758,917,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arofaniana">
<emphasis box="[758,917,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. arofaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Eyes spherical or elliptical, not emarginate. Antennae of males usually reaching posterior margin of pronotum or beyond, antennae of females shorter, not reaching posterior margin of pronotum. Funicle thin, then antennal club 3-segmented (most species) or 4-segmented (in 
<taxonomicName box="[189,286,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[189,286,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or antennomeres continuously extended (e.g. in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryzna &amp; Banar" authorityYear="2022" box="[843,999,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arofaniana">
<emphasis box="[843,999,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. arofaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Dorsal transverse carina of pronotum distinct and antebasal, pronotal declivity wide. Medium- or large-sized species, from 
<quantity box="[1107,1172,1832,1859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
(small specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fairmaire, 1892)" baseAuthorityName="Fairmaire" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. rubricollis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fairmaire, L. M. H." box="[284,469,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" pagination="168 - 172" refId="ref7977" refString="Fairmaire, L. M. H. (1892) [Descriptions de quelques Coleopteres de Madagascar, provenant de la region de Diego Suarez]. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, Bulletin 61, 168 - 172." type="journal article" year="1892">Fairmaire, 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryzna &amp; Banar" authorityYear="2022" box="[488,645,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arofaniana">
<emphasis box="[488,645,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. arofaniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to more than 
<quantity box="[810,889,1868,1895]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse, 1877" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1877" box="[905,1257,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivaceus">
<emphasis box="[905,1045,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">D. olivaceus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse, C. O." box="[1052,1257,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref9594" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. (1877) Descriptions of twenty new species of Coleoptera from various localities. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1877, 1 - 13. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1877. tb 02897. x" type="journal article" year="1877">Waterhouse, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1904,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="31">Terminalia.</emphasis>
Male and female genitalia compared to overall size of body conspicuously small. Female genitalia: ovipositor short and wide, hemisternites strikingly short and delicate, without toothed plates, with only small preapical stylus. Lateral and median rods very short, median rod reaching to ca. half of the length of lateral rod. Transverse bar invisible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,853,150,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
Remarks on terminalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[576,627,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<emphasis box="[731,853,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1866" box="[731,848,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Diastatotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">D. tigrina</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Male: Aedeagus smaller, pedon and tectum wide, apodemes moderately curved.Apex of pedon completely straight, apex of tectum narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1328,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[168,1432,503,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,489,1925]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Diastatotropis tigrina Lacordaire, 1866, Moramanga env., male; 1, dorsal habitus; 2, aedeagus in dorsal view; 3, tegmen in ventral view. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6388823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6388823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Tegmen (
<figureCitation box="[160,227,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[168,1432,503,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,489,1925]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Diastatotropis tigrina Lacordaire, 1866, Moramanga env., male; 1, dorsal habitus; 2, aedeagus in dorsal view; 3, tegmen in ventral view. Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6388823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6388823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) relatively robust and long, tegminal plate rather narrow, its sides bent, apex of tegmen with long, distinct setae. Basal piece with two conspicuous spurs oriented posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis box="[199,283,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Female</emphasis>
: Pygidium (
<figureCitation box="[422,489,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[179,1409,184,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Diastatotropis tigrina Lacordaire, 1866, Moramanga env., female terminalia; 4, pygidium; 5, sternite VIII; 6, tergite VIII; 7, ovipositor in ventral view; 8, apex of ovipositor in ventral view (arrows indicate sclerotized parts). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6388825" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6388825/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) broad, roughly sclerotized. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[969,1035,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[179,1409,184,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[179,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Diastatotropis tigrina Lacordaire, 1866, Moramanga env., female terminalia; 4, pygidium; 5, sternite VIII; 6, tergite VIII; 7, ovipositor in ventral view; 8, apex of ovipositor in ventral view (arrows indicate sclerotized parts). Scale bars in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6388825" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6388825/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="32">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
